'''絕對真空'''（{{lang-en|'''Absolute vacuum'''}}），亦作'''完美真空'''（{{lang|en|'''Perfect vacuum'''}}）<ref name=about>{{cite web |url=http://chemistry.about.com/od/chemistryglossary/g/Absolute-Vacuum-Definition.htm |title=Definition of Absolute Vacuum |trans_title=絕對真空的定義 |publisher=[[about.com|about.com]] |accessdate=2014-03-29 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140710022332/http://chemistry.about.com/od/chemistryglossary/g/Absolute-Vacuum-Definition.htm |archivedate=2014-07-10 }}</ref>，是指一個理论上沒有任何[[物質|物質]]的封闭的空间，是一种[[理論|理論]]上理想的[[真空|真空]]狀態（[[氣壓|氣壓]]＝0），以目前的科技尚難達到。

在[[壓力測量|壓力測量]]領域，由於現代許多高精密度的產品在製造過程中的某些階段必需使用程度不一的真空才能製造，絕對真空是真空技術中按照壓力的高低而區分的五個級別的最高級別，內裡只有0 [[Torr|Torr]]，比其次一級的[[超高真空|超高真空]]（[[Ultra-High_Vacuum|Ultra-High Vacuum]]）所要求的10<sup>-7</sup> Torr以下還要嚴謹。

另外，在[[古典電磁學|古典電磁學]]的定義，完美真空是電磁效應的一個標準參考媒介<ref name=weig>{{cite book
 | title = Introduction to complex mediums for optics and electromagnetics
 | author = Werner S. Weiglhofer
 | editor= Werner S. Weiglhofer and Akhlesh Lakhtakia, eds
 | publisher = SPIE Press
 | chapter=§ 4.1 The classical vacuum as reference medium
 | year = 2003
 | isbn = 978-0-8194-4947-4
 | pages = 28, 34
 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=QtIP_Lr3gngC&pg=PA34
 }}</ref><ref name="Progress">
{{cite book
 | title = Progress in Optics, Volume 51
 | chapter = Electromagnetic Fields in Linear Bianisotropic Mediums
 | author = Tom G. MacKay
 | editor = Emil Wolf
 | publisher = Elsevier
 | year = 2008
 | isbn = 978-0-444-52038-8
 | page = 143
 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=lCm9Q18P8cMC&pg=PA143
 }}</ref>，所以亦有作者把這種真空狀態稱為「'''古典真空'''」<ref name=weig/>，以與[[量子力學|量子力學]]其他有關真空的[[術語|術語]]如「[[量子電動力學真空|量子電動力學真空]]」（QED vacuum）或「[[量子色動力學真空|量子色動力學真空]]」（QCD vacuum）等透過可以產生短暫的[[虛粒子|虛粒子]]密度和[[相對介電常數|相對介電常數]]與[[相對磁導率|相對磁導率]]兩項並不統一的[[真空波動|真空波動]]環境<ref name=Grynberg>
{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=l-l0L8YInA0C&pg=PA341 |page=341 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2010 |title=Introduction to Quantum Optics: From the Semi-Classical Approach to Quantized Light |quote=...deals with the quantum vacuum where, in contrast to the classical vacuum, radiation has properties, in particular, fluctuations, with which one can associate physical effects. |isbn=0-521-55112-9 |author=Gilbert Grynberg, Alain Aspect, Claude Fabre}}

